
"Y-You'll be okay?" I mentally smacked myself in the head; that sounded more like a question than a statement. Good job, Taylor, you're still no good at comforting people! Learn from Ben at least! "Think about it. After four more days, your parents have to let you eat all the chocolates you want!"
Sakura ignored my tone and flipped herself back onto her stomach. "Yeah, I guess." Then her head lifted up from her arms. Her usual bright smile returned back to her face. I held in a breath as the green-eyed girl stood up on the side of her bed. "Come on, are we gonna continue the game or what?!"